snippet.textDisplay:
Actually, people may disagree with me (and that's totally fine), but I think that this song - in my opinion, of course - was genuinely nothing without him.

He actually sits on this track stylistically and vocally a lot better than Samra.  The way he emphasised his phrasing, used all the Western ideas of melodies (I am a trained Western Vocalist) is actually what I have been looking for in a Coke Studio vocalist for a very long time.

He is creative.  So damn clever with his vocal placement - and, that translated with the way he brought his style and married it so effortlessly with the groove of this song.

He is, actually, the first Coke Studio vocalist who has blended contemporary Western Singing concepts into his vocal and delivered it into a song.  Which is what Coke Studio is all about.  Fusion music.

Western 'feel' is not just using English in songs, adding jazz elements to your music, or, using western instruments.  It's also using the vocal to add texture and layers in the song - which he did so damn perfectly.

Coke Studio, you have my respect.  This vocalist is definitely my favourite.
